This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science - Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with malware detection and the identification of hidden malicious code. It also involves machine learning models, which could place it in the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of wavelet transforms, which could place it in the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
